title: Expository Weather Visualization
description: Data visualization that uses expressive visual design choices to demonstrate a weather trend in San Diego compared to other US cities. Data collected from https://www.usclimatedata.com/.

title: Deceptive Data Visualization
description: Data visualization that uses deceptive tactics to push a specific narrative, based on data from this physionet study about Tai Chi: https://physionet.org/content/taichidb/1.0.2/.

title: Expectation Maximization Algorithm
description: Implementation of Expectation Maximization Algorithm for CSE150A on a dataset of student participants reporting which movies they liked out of a given set of popular films. Check out the repo here: https://github.com/angela-shen/Projects/tree/main/Expectation%20Maximization%20(EM)%20Algorithm

title: Math 189 California Housing Data Group Project
description: Math 189 group project that investigates US housing data and runs various data transformations and statistical tests. Check out the repo here: https://github.com/angela-shen/Math189-group33

title: Analyzing Relationships Between Minutes and Ratings of Recipes - DSC80 Final Project
description: Final Project for DSC80, collaborated with Kendall Underwood to study trends and create a sophisticated prediction model. Check out the repo here: https://github.com/PandaFalls2004/Minutes_and_Ratings. Check out our website here: https://pandafalls2004.github.io/Minutes_and_Ratings/

title: Conway's Game of Life
description: Implementation of Conway's Game of Life for UCSC CSE13s, which can be played on the command line.

title: Schmidt Samoa Cryptography
description: Implementation of Schmidt Samoa cryptography. Produces public and private keys to encrypt and decrypt files. Uses gnu's gmp (gnu multi-precision library).
